Multiple studies have found that property crime and even drug-related crime have no effect on home values.
This has huge ramifications for everything from property values, to business investment, to simple consumer perceptions.
Selling a house in these areas can be difficult, especially if the danger factors have negatively impacted the property values in the area.
Unfortunately, we know that property crime has very little impact on home values, while violent crime has a huge impact.
It had the ninth-most violent crime, the seventh-most property crime, the fourth-most natural disasters, and the sixth-most transportation fatalities.